By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Former President Goodluck Jonathan has warned Bayelsa state People Democratic Party(PDP) chapter to get its act together or risk loosing the forthcoming governorship poll in the state the All Progressive Congress(APC). Jonathan, who made this known during the PDP Elders Advisory Council meeting at the Government House in Yenagoa, stressed that it is only unity with the PDP that can guarantee victory of the party in the November 16 governorship poll. His words: “I need to plead with all the aspirants and all political leaders that there should be no mudslinging. We must free the space and eschew rancour because finally one person will become the candidate of the party and for that one person to win the election, all aspirants must work for that person. “It is only our unity that can give us victory and if we are not united, they (APC) can get away with it.  